mibinternetProfileTable.name: mibinternetProfileTable
mibinternetProfileTable.description: A list of mibinternetProfile profile entries.

mibinternetProfileEntry.name: mibinternetProfileEntry
mibinternetProfileEntry.description: A mibinternetProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibinternetProfile profile.

internetProfile_Station.name: internetProfile_Station
internetProfile_Station.description: The name of the host we will be communicating with. This name is used as part of the authentication process when authentication is being used.

internetProfile_Active.name: internetProfile_Active
internetProfile_Active.description: A profile can be disabled by setting this field to no. There is no difference between an inactive profile and no profile at all to the remainder of the code.

internetProfile_EncapsulationProtocol.name: internetProfile_EncapsulationProtocol
internetProfile_EncapsulationProtocol.description: The encapsulation protocol to be used when communicating with the named station.

internetProfile_CalledNumberType.name: internetProfile_CalledNumberType
internetProfile_CalledNumberType.description: Indication of whether national number, international number, etc. is specified.

internetProfile_DialNumber.name: internetProfile_DialNumber
internetProfile_DialNumber.description: The phone number of the named station.

internetProfile_SubAddress.name: internetProfile_SubAddress
internetProfile_SubAddress.description: The sub-address extension to the dialed number of the station.

internetProfile_Clid.name: internetProfile_Clid
internetProfile_Clid.description: The calling line number for authentication.

internetProfile_AutoProfiles.name: internetProfile_AutoProfiles
internetProfile_AutoProfiles.description: This parameter enables or disables automatic profile creation. Currently only the Stinger IDSL provides this capability for PPP Circuits and Frame Relay Circuits.

internetProfile_IpOptions_IpRoutingEnabl.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_IpRoutingEnabled
internetProfile_IpOptions_IpRoutingEnabl.description: Enable/disable IP routing for this connection.

internetProfile_IpOptions_VjHeaderPredic.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_VjHeaderPrediction
internetProfile_IpOptions_VjHeaderPredic.description: Enable/disable Van Jacabson TCP Header prediction processing on this connection if supported by the selected encapsulation protocol.

internetProfile_IpOptions_RemoteAddress.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_RemoteAddress
internetProfile_IpOptions_RemoteAddress.description: The remote address with netmask of the named host.

internetProfile_IpOptions_NetmaskRemote.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_NetmaskRemote
internetProfile_IpOptions_NetmaskRemote.description: The netmask of the remote address.

internetProfile_IpOptions_LocalAddress.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_LocalAddress
internetProfile_IpOptions_LocalAddress.description: The interface address with netmask, if required, of the local end. If left zero the interface is assumed to be an unnumbered interface.

internetProfile_IpOptions_NetmaskLocal.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_NetmaskLocal
internetProfile_IpOptions_NetmaskLocal.description: The netmask of the local interface address.

internetProfile_IpOptions_RoutingMetric.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_RoutingMetric
internetProfile_IpOptions_RoutingMetric.description: The routing metric, typically measured in number of hops, to be used in the routing table entry created for this connection when the connection is active.

internetProfile_IpOptions_Preference.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_Preference
internetProfile_IpOptions_Preference.description: The preference used for comparing this route to other routes. Preference has a higher priority than metric. As with the metric field, the lower the number, the higher the preference.

internetProfile_IpOptions_DownPreference.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_DownPreference
internetProfile_IpOptions_DownPreference.description: The preference used for comparing the down-metric route to other routes. Preference has a higher priority than metric. As with the metric field, the lower the number, the higher the preference.

internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRoute.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRoute
internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRoute.description: Enable/disable distribution of the route created for this connection via routing protocols. Private routes are used internally, but never advertized to the outside world.

internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastAllow.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastAllowed
internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastAllow.description: Enable this connection as a multicast traffic client.

internetProfile_IpOptions_AddressPool.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_AddressPool
internetProfile_IpOptions_AddressPool.description: The number of the address pool from which an address for this host should be obtained when using assigned addresses.

internetProfile_IpOptions_IpDirect.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_IpDirect
internetProfile_IpOptions_IpDirect.description: The address of the next-hop when IP direct routing is used.

internetProfile_IpOptions_Rip.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_Rip
internetProfile_IpOptions_Rip.description: Specify if RIP or RIP-2 should be used over this connection and if used in both directions or not.

internetProfile_IpOptions_RouteFilter.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_RouteFilter
internetProfile_IpOptions_RouteFilter.description: The name of this filter. All filters are referenced by name so a name must be assigned to active filters.

internetProfile_IpOptions_SourceIpCheck.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_SourceIpCheck
internetProfile_IpOptions_SourceIpCheck.description: Enable/disable source ip checking. Packets with source ip address which doesn't match with negotiated remote ip address will be dropped.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Ac.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Active
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Ac.description: Is OSPF active on this interface.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Ar.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Area
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Ar.description: The area that this interface belongs to.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Ar.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_AreaType
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Ar.description: The type of Area. Normal, Stub, NSSA

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Pr.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Priority
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Pr.description: The priority of this router in DR elections.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Au.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_AuthenType
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Au.description: The type of OSPF authentication in effect.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Ke.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_KeyId
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Ke.description: The key identifier for MD5 authentication.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Do.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_DownCost
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Do.description: The output cost when the link is physically down but virtually up.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_As.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_AseType
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_As.description: The OSPF ASE type of this LSA.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_As.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_AseTag
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_As.description: The OSPF ASE tag of this link.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_No.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_NonMulticast
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_No.description: Use direct addresses instead of multicast addresses.

internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Po.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_PollInterval
internetProfile_IpOptions_OspfOptions_Po.description: The poll interval for non-broadcast multi-access network (seconds).

internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastRateL.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastRateLimit
internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastRateL.description: The multicast rate limit in seconds.

internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastGroup.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastGroupLeaveDelay
internetProfile_IpOptions_MulticastGroup.description: The multicast group leave in seconds. This is only for IGMP Version 2

internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientDnsAddrA.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientDnsAddrAssign
internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientDnsAddrA.description: A flag to control assigning user specific DNS Addresses.

internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientDefaultG.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientDefaultGateway
internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientDefaultG.description: The default gateway to be used for traffic from this connection, if no specific route is found in the routing table. If left zero, the system's default route will be used.

internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Act.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Active
internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Act.description: Activate type of service for this connection.

internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Pre.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Precedence
internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Pre.description: Tag the precedence bits (priority bits) in the TOS octet of IP datagram header with this value when match occurs.

internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Typ.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_TypeOfService
internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Typ.description: Tag the type of service field in the TOS octet of IP datagram header with this value when match occurs.

internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_App.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_ApplyTo
internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_App.description: Define how the type-of-service applies to data flow for this connection.

internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Dsc.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Dscp
internetProfile_IpOptions_TosOptions_Dsc.description: DSCP tag to be used in marking of the packets (if marking-type = dscp).

internetProfile_IpOptions_TosFilter.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_TosFilter
internetProfile_IpOptions_TosFilter.description: The name of type-of-service filter. All filters are referenced by name so a name must be assigned to active filters.

internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientWinsAddr.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientWinsAddrAssign
internetProfile_IpOptions_ClientWinsAddr.description: A flag to control assigning user specific WINS Addresses.

internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRouteTa.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRouteTable
internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRouteTa.description: Private route table ID for this connection

internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRoutePr.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRouteProfileRequired
internetProfile_IpOptions_PrivateRoutePr.description: Parameter to decide default action,if private route table not found. If set to yes, the call will be cleared if the private route profile cannot be found. If set to no, the call will be allowed to complete, even if the private route profile cannot be found.

internetProfile_IpOptions_NatProfileName.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_NatProfileName
internetProfile_IpOptions_NatProfileName.description: The profile to use for NAT translations on this connection.

internetProfile_IpOptions_AddressRealm.name: internetProfile_IpOptions_AddressRealm
internetProfile_IpOptions_AddressRealm.description: Used to determine which interfaces and WANs are connected to the same address space--they will have the identical values in this field.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxRoutingEna.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxRoutingEnabled
internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxRoutingEna.description: Enable/disable IPX routing for this connection.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_PeerMode.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_PeerMode
internetProfile_IpxOptions_PeerMode.description: Enable/disable full routing between peer or use the pool to assign a network number.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_Rip.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_Rip
internetProfile_IpxOptions_Rip.description: This field specifies RIP traffic when peer is a Router.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_Sap.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_Sap
internetProfile_IpxOptions_Sap.description: This field specifies SAP traffic when peer is a Router.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_DialQuery.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_DialQuery
internetProfile_IpxOptions_DialQuery.description: Indicate if we should dial to this connection if our SAP table contains no NetWare file servers, and a workstation makes a get-nearest-server query.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_NetNumber.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_NetNumber
internetProfile_IpxOptions_NetNumber.description: The network number of the other router. May be zero, if we don't know what it is.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_NetAlias.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_NetAlias
internetProfile_IpxOptions_NetAlias.description: The network number of the point to point link.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_SapFilter.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_SapFilter
internetProfile_IpxOptions_SapFilter.description: The name of the IPX SAP filter, if any, to use with this connection.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxSpoofing.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxSpoofing
internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxSpoofing.description: Selects the IPX spoofing mode when bridging.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxSapHsProxy.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxSapHsProxy
internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxSapHsProxy.description: Use IPX SAP Home Server Proxy.

internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxHeaderComp.name: internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxHeaderCompression
internetProfile_IpxOptions_IpxHeaderComp.description: Use IPX header compression if encapsulation supports it.

internetProfile_BridgingOptions_Bridging.name: internetProfile_BridgingOptions_BridgingGroup
internetProfile_BridgingOptions_Bridging.description: Select the bridging group for this connection. Group 0 disables bridging. All packets not routed will be bridged to interfaces belonging to the same group.

internetProfile_BridgingOptions_DialOnBr.name: internetProfile_BridgingOptions_DialOnBroadcast
internetProfile_BridgingOptions_DialOnBr.description: Enable/disable outdial when broadcast frames are received.

internetProfile_BridgingOptions_IpxSpoof.name: internetProfile_BridgingOptions_IpxSpoofing
internetProfile_BridgingOptions_IpxSpoof.description: Selects the IPX spoofing mode when bridging.

internetProfile_BridgingOptions_Fill2.name: internetProfile_BridgingOptions_Fill2
internetProfile_BridgingOptions_Fill2.description: filler to get to 32 bit boundary

internetProfile_BridgingOptions_Egress.name: internetProfile_BridgingOptions_Egress
internetProfile_BridgingOptions_Egress.description: Enable/disable Egress on this interface. This interface will become the exit path for all packets destined to the network.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_CallFilte.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_CallFilter
internetProfile_SessionOptions_CallFilte.description: The name of the filter used to determine if a packet should cause the idle timer to be reset or, when the answer profile is used for connection profile defaults, if a call should be placed.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_DataFilte.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_DataFilter
internetProfile_SessionOptions_DataFilte.description: The name of the filter used to determine if packets should be forwarded or dropped.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_FilterPer.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_FilterPersistence
internetProfile_SessionOptions_FilterPer.description: Determines if filters should persist between calls.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_FilterReq.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_FilterRequired
internetProfile_SessionOptions_FilterReq.description: If No, the call will be allowed to come up even if the specified filter was not found either locally, in the cache or in RADIUS. If Yes, then the call will be cleared if the specified filter was not found either locally, in the cache or in RADIUS.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_IdleTimer.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_IdleTimer
internetProfile_SessionOptions_IdleTimer.description: The number of seconds of no activity before a call will be dropped. The value 0 disables the idle timer.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_TsIdleMod.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_TsIdleMode
internetProfile_SessionOptions_TsIdleMod.description: The method used to determine when the terminal server idle session timer is reset.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_TsIdleTim.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_TsIdleTimer
internetProfile_SessionOptions_TsIdleTim.description: The number of seconds of no activity as defined by the idle mode before a session will be terminated.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_Backup.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_Backup
internetProfile_SessionOptions_Backup.description: Name of the backup connection profile.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_Secondary.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_Secondary
internetProfile_SessionOptions_Secondary.description: A secondary internet profile used for dial back-up support.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxCallDu.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxCallDuration
internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxCallDu.description: The number of minutes of connect time before a call will be dropped. The value 0 disables the connection timer.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_VtpGatewa.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_VtpGateway
internetProfile_SessionOptions_VtpGatewa.description: This profile is an VTP gateway connection to an mobile client's home network.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_Blockcoun.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_Blockcountlimit
internetProfile_SessionOptions_Blockcoun.description: Maximum number of failed attempts allowed for connection before blocking the call.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_Blockdura.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_Blockduration
internetProfile_SessionOptions_Blockdura.description: Number of seconds that connection attempts to non responding network will be blocked before allowing retries.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxVtpTun.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxVtpTunnels
internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxVtpTun.description: If this profile is a VTP gateway, then this parameter specifies the maximum number of VTP tunnels allowed to the VTP home network specified by the name of this profile.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_RedialDel.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_RedialDelayLimit
internetProfile_SessionOptions_RedialDel.description: Number of seconds delay before allowing a redial

internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslCa.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslCapUpRate
internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslCa.description: The per session adsl-cap up stream data rate

internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslCa.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslCapDownRate
internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslCa.description: The per session adsl-cap down stream data rate

internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesSdslRa.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesSdslRate
internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesSdslRa.description: The per session symetrical data rate. This parameter does not pertain to the old 16 port sdsl card.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslDm.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslDmtUpRate
internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslDm.description: The per session adsl-dmt up stream data rate

internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslDm.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslDmtDownRate
internetProfile_SessionOptions_SesAdslDm.description: The per session adsl-dmt down stream data rate

internetProfile_SessionOptions_RxDataRat.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_RxDataRateLimit
internetProfile_SessionOptions_RxDataRat.description: The maximum information rate to be received from the named station (kbps).

internetProfile_SessionOptions_TxDataRat.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_TxDataRateLimit
internetProfile_SessionOptions_TxDataRat.description: The maximum information rate to be transmitted to the named station (kbps).

internetProfile_SessionOptions_TrafficSh.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_TrafficShaper
internetProfile_SessionOptions_TrafficSh.description: The traffic shaper assigned to this profile.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxtapLog.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxtapLogServer
internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxtapLog.description: The name or the IP Address of the host to which the MaxTap start/stop notifications has to be sent.

internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxtapDat.name: internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxtapDataServer
internetProfile_SessionOptions_MaxtapDat.description: The name or the IP Address of the host to which the tapped data has to be sent.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_AnswerOrigi.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_AnswerOriginate
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_AnswerOrigi.description: Specifies if this profile can be used for incoming calls, outgoing calls, or both.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Callback.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Callback
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Callback.description: When true a call received from the named host requires callback security. The number dialed is the phoneNumber from this connection profile.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_CallType.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_CallType
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_CallType.description: Nailed channel usage for this connection.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_NailedGroup.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_NailedGroups
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_NailedGroup.description: All the nailed groups belonging to a session. MPP supports multiple groups.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Ft1Caller.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Ft1Caller
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Ft1Caller.description: Specifies if this side should initiate calls when a mix of nailed and switched calls are being used.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Force56kbps.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Force56kbps
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_Force56kbps.description: If yes then inbound 64 kbps calls are connected at 56 kbps.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DataService.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DataService
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DataService.description: The type of bearer channel capability to set up for each switched call in the session.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_CallByCall.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_CallByCall
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_CallByCall.description: The call-by-call signaling value for PRI lines.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_BillingNumb.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_BillingNumber
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_BillingNumb.description: A number used for billing purposes. This number, if present, is used as either a 'billing suffix' or the 'calling party number'.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_TransitNumb.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_TransitNumber
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_TransitNumb.description: The string for use in the 'transit network IE' for PRI calling when going through a LEC.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_ExpectCallb.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_ExpectCallback
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_ExpectCallb.description: When true we expect calls to the named host will result in a callback from that host. This would occur if the remote host were authenticating us based on Caller ID.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DialoutAllo.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DialoutAllowed
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DialoutAllo.description: When true, this connection is allowed to use the LAN modems to place outgoing calls.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DelayCallba.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DelayCallback
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_DelayCallba.description: Number of seconds to delay before dialing back. Values of 0-3 seconds are treated as 3 seconds.

internetProfile_TelcoOptions_NasPortType.name: internetProfile_TelcoOptions_NasPortType
internetProfile_TelcoOptions_NasPortType.description: Indicates the type of physical port being used.

internetProfile_PppOptions_SendAuthMode.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_SendAuthMode
internetProfile_PppOptions_SendAuthMode.description: The type of PPP authentication to use for this call.

internetProfile_PppOptions_PppCircuit.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_PppCircuit
internetProfile_PppOptions_PppCircuit.description: PPP Circuit. Set to type to enable the PPP Circuit Mode.

internetProfile_PppOptions_PppCircuitNam.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_PppCircuitName
internetProfile_PppOptions_PppCircuitNam.description: The peer datalink identifier for a PPP circuit.

internetProfile_PppOptions_BiDirectional.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_BiDirectionalAuth
internetProfile_PppOptions_BiDirectional.description: This parameter enables the authentication to be done in both directions. It can be used only with CHAP or MS-CHAP authentication.

internetProfile_PppOptions_SendPassword.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_SendPassword
internetProfile_PppOptions_SendPassword.description: This is the password sent to the far end; used for MPP and PPP PAP and CHAP security.

internetProfile_PppOptions_SubstituteSen.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_SubstituteSendName
internetProfile_PppOptions_SubstituteSen.description: Name send to the far end, if different from the global system name.

internetProfile_PppOptions_RecvPassword.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_RecvPassword
internetProfile_PppOptions_RecvPassword.description: This is the password received from the far end; used for MPP and PPP PAP and CHAP security.

internetProfile_PppOptions_SubstituteRec.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_SubstituteRecvName
internetProfile_PppOptions_SubstituteRec.description: Name expected from the far end used during a bi-directional authentication. If it is null the profile name will be used in place. This parameter is used only for outgoing calls.

internetProfile_PppOptions_LinkCompressi.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_LinkCompression
internetProfile_PppOptions_LinkCompressi.description: The type of link compression to use for PPP, MP, and MPP calls.

internetProfile_PppOptions_Mru.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_Mru
internetProfile_PppOptions_Mru.description: The Maximum Receive Unit, i.e. the largest frame we will accept.

internetProfile_PppOptions_Lqm.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_Lqm
internetProfile_PppOptions_Lqm.description: Link Quality Monitoring. Set to Yes to enable the PPP LQM protocol.

internetProfile_PppOptions_LqmMinimumPer.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_LqmMinimumPeriod
internetProfile_PppOptions_LqmMinimumPer.description: The minimum period, in 1/100 of a second, that we will accept/send link quality monitoring packets.

internetProfile_PppOptions_LqmMaximumPer.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_LqmMaximumPeriod
internetProfile_PppOptions_LqmMaximumPer.description: The maximum period, in 1/100 of a second, that we will accept/send link quality monitoring packets.

internetProfile_PppOptions_CbcpEnabled.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_CbcpEnabled
internetProfile_PppOptions_CbcpEnabled.description: Enable Microsoft Callback Control Protocol Negotiation.

internetProfile_PppOptions_ModeCallbackC.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_ModeCallbackControl
internetProfile_PppOptions_ModeCallbackC.description: CBCP operation allowed on to use for this call.

internetProfile_PppOptions_DelayCallback.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_DelayCallbackControl
internetProfile_PppOptions_DelayCallback.description: Delay to request before callback to us is initiated

internetProfile_PppOptions_TrunkGroupCal.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_TrunkGroupCallbackControl
internetProfile_PppOptions_TrunkGroupCal.description: Trunk group to use for the callback.

internetProfile_PppOptions_SplitCodeDotU.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_SplitCodeDotUserEnabled
internetProfile_PppOptions_SplitCodeDotU.description: TRUE if local splitting of passwords is desired in CACHE-TOKEN. This feature permits the use of usernames longer than five chars, when using a typical 4 digit pin and 6 digit ACE token code.

internetProfile_PppOptions_PppInterfaceT.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_PppInterfaceType
internetProfile_PppOptions_PppInterfaceT.description: PPP network interface for this profile.

internetProfile_PppOptions_Mtu.name: internetProfile_PppOptions_Mtu
internetProfile_PppOptions_Mtu.description: The Maximum Transmit Unit, i.e. the largest frame we will transmit.

internetProfile_MpOptions_BaseChannelCou.name: internetProfile_MpOptions_BaseChannelCount
internetProfile_MpOptions_BaseChannelCou.description: When the session is initially set up, and if it is a fixed session, the number of channels to be used for the call.

internetProfile_MpOptions_MinimumChannel.name: internetProfile_MpOptions_MinimumChannels
internetProfile_MpOptions_MinimumChannel.description: The default value for the minimum number of channels in a multi-channel call.

internetProfile_MpOptions_MaximumChannel.name: internetProfile_MpOptions_MaximumChannels
internetProfile_MpOptions_MaximumChannel.description: The default value for the maximum number of channels in a multi-channel call.

internetProfile_MppOptions_AuxSendPasswo.name: internetProfile_MppOptions_AuxSendPassword
internetProfile_MppOptions_AuxSendPasswo.description: This is the password sent to the far end; used for MPP PAP-TOKEN-CHAP security.

internetProfile_MppOptions_DynamicAlgori.name: internetProfile_MppOptions_DynamicAlgorithm
internetProfile_MppOptions_DynamicAlgori.description: The algorithm to use to calculate the average link utilization. Bandwidth changes are performed on the average utilization, not current utilization.

internetProfile_MppOptions_BandwidthMoni.name: internetProfile_MppOptions_BandwidthMonitorDirection
internetProfile_MppOptions_BandwidthMoni.description: The direction to monitor link utilization. A unit can monitor transmit, transmit and receive, or turn off monitoring entirely.

internetProfile_MppOptions_IncrementChan.name: internetProfile_MppOptions_IncrementChannelCount
internetProfile_MppOptions_IncrementChan.description: Number of channels to increment as a block.

internetProfile_MppOptions_DecrementChan.name: internetProfile_MppOptions_DecrementChannelCount
internetProfile_MppOptions_DecrementChan.description: Number of channels to decrement as a block.

internetProfile_MppOptions_SecondsHistor.name: internetProfile_MppOptions_SecondsHistory
internetProfile_MppOptions_SecondsHistor.description: The number of seconds of history that link utilization is averaged over to make bandwidth changes.
